# Dependency Rules

Before adding any dependency:
1. Check if the functionality exists already in the codebase
2. Check if a built-in library covers the use case
3. Evaluate: bundle size, license, maintenance status (last commit, open issues)
4. Document the justification in the PR description
5. Never add a library to solve a problem under 20 lines of code

Banned patterns:
- Moment.js → use date-fns or native Intl
- Lodash for single utility functions → use native JS
- Multiple HTTP client libraries in the same project
- Any library with a GPL license in commercial projects

Security:
- npm audit must pass (no high or critical) in CI
- pip audit must pass (no high or critical) in CI
- Dependabot or Renovate must be configured on every repo
